				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Commercials that are broadcast on TV have to use a picture signal that conforms to the NTSC spec. The standard horizontal period is 341.25 dots (227.5 color subcarrier cycles so that successive lines are out of phase), not 341 or 340, and the standard picture height is 262.5 lines, not 262. There must have been some way to convert the footage for standard TV use.<br /><br />How did genlock work in the Famicom Titler?<br /><br />On a rewatch, it looks like they somehow scaled the video. Ice Climber, for example, is zoomed in at one point. I'm thinking something with an RGB PPU.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

