					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, sorry for not doing more technical analysis on my Titler.<br /><br />IIRC, if you feed interlaced video into the Titler, the Genlocked video output is also interlaced.  Feed it noninterlaced, and it remains noninterlaced.<br /><br />As for how it synchs... I remember when I connected/disconnected video for overlaying, the sound on the Famicom noticeably got slower for a split-second.  I reckon it does some voodoo with the CPU/PPU crystals via a PLL or somesuch to keep both video sources in sync.</div>

					
